        "timestamp": "2017-07-26 00:02:11.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\n(6 comments)\n\nChenfei, the script should work in theory in a drools docker container.   Your set up may be a little different, but as long as it is unix based, and as long you are building there, all artifacts should be in your local directory. If you look at the script, the failing line, is just trying to execute $M2_HOME/bin/mvn command, you could just tweak the script locally to call \"mvn\" directly if it is in your path.   Just a way to get some minor assurance, very minor, so if it is a big deal, don't bother.\n\nThe archetype directory inner pom.xml (there are 2, first one for the archetype definition) should look similar to what you have in controlloop/templates/template.demo.v1.0.0/template.demo/pom.xml.   Again, similar pattern, pre-restructuring changes, if you can make sure those files, are up to date as well.",
        "patchset_number": 4
      },
